==Indonesian==
{{wikipedia||lang=id}}
===Etymology===
From {{bor|id|ja|-}} {{ja-r|焼肉|やきにく|lit=grilled meat}}.
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|id|[jakiˈniku]}}
* {{hyphenation|id|ya|ki|ni|ku}}
===Noun===
{{id-noun|head=|pl=-}}
# {{lb|id|cooking}} {{l|en|yakiniku}}: a style of cooking bite-size meat (usually beef and offal) and vegetables on gridirons or griddles over a flame of wood charcoals carbonized by dry distillation (sumibi, {{l|ja|炭火}}) or a gas/electric grill.
